text.tspan: Alcohol consumption vs. GDP per capita, 2018
Average annual alcohol consumption measured in liters of pure alcohol per person aged 15 years or older.
Note: Gross domestic product (GDP) per capita is adjusted for differences in price levels between countries (measured in international-$).
Data source: World Health Organization (via World Bank), Data compiled from multiple sources by World Bank
